        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 8:20PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 819 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northwest of White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newlan Creek Reservoir and Fort Logan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
